shared_text:
Main Street Elementary School & Kindergarten Center
June 4 at 12:09 PM ·

Main Street & Kindergarten (19'-20') Yearbooks just delivered!

Ideally, these would have been delivered in time to put in the "bag it & tag it" system for curb-side pick-up w/ other student items.

However, Inter-State Studio was not at full capacity in operation during the COVID-19 safety measures & put their timelines behind. We are very sorry for the inconvenience.

Susan Miller (Secretary) is the main point of contact.
She will be available in the office until at least 2:30 PM today... & tomorrow (8:00 AM - 2:30 PM) is also an "open" option.

If an alternate time is needed, please call the Main Street School office @ 217-774-4731 & schedule a time/date w/ Susan. If that will not work either, you may have to wait until we come back in the fall but we are trying to get you some options now.

We did order a few (not as many as typical) "extras" in case you didn't order one but your child does want one. .

post_text:
You may have heard news last week that all graduation events of any sort had been cancelled by the Illinois State Board of Education. Although that was certainly discouraging, we fully anticipated revisions to follow quickly thereafter.

This weekend, ISBE retracted their executive order giving school districts authority in the local decision making process.

All events and experiences that were previously communicated will carry on as planned. During all events, we will adhere to health and safety recommendations, which will require a strict communication plan and complete compliance.

In keeping with our prior practice, we will continue to communicate with our partner organizations throughout the community in making sure we can safely provide all of these ceremonial experiences, and that each event is effectively organized.

Wishing you all well, always.

Kyle Ladd | SHS Principal

Illinois State Board of Education
May 1 at 9:24 AM ·

ISBE is developing updated recommendations for graduation ceremonies in consultation with the Illinois Department of Public Health (IDPH) to align with the new disaster proclamation and updated stay-at-home order that the Governor enacted yesterday.

The safety and wellbeing of students, families, and educators must be the number one priority.

However, we understand the milestone that graduation ceremonies represent in our lives and are developing guidelines that encourage creative alternatives to the traditional graduation ceremony.

post_text: We LOVE our RAM Readers!
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
“Thank You, Mr. Falker” -Patricia Polacco READ-Aloud w/ Mr. Scott

Main Street Elementary School & Kindergarten Center
March 19 at 3:19 PM ·

Learning to READ is so POWERFUL...but not always easy. I hope you can remember what it was like learning to read & our earliest readers know to keep practicing. The best readers read often. We wish for our kids & students to find joy in reading. Witnessing a young reader emerge will make you cry; it is really that special. This story showcases the impact of positive adults in young childrens' lives w/ important lessons on not giving up & how we should really treat people.

FREE Meals to ALL of our Kids available...so easy to sign-up!
We are in this together, RAMS Family!
shared_text:
Main Street Elementary School & Kindergarten Center
March 17 at 10:31 AM ·

Shelbyville Families! We have FREE FOOD for our kids...FREE to ALL of our Shelbyville kids & siblings 18 under! It is so easy to sign-up...we just need (3) details. We can deliver to babysitter / daycares as well.
1. child(ren) name(s) & age(s) - i.e. John Doe-7 & Jane Doe-9
2. delivery method - (3) OPTIONS
(A) pick-up @ Main Street @ (9:00 AM - 11:00 AM) @ NW entrance (by ramp)
(B) pick-up @ Moulton @ (9:00 AM - 11:00 AM) @ drive-thru
(C) home delivery...we need the address for delivery
3. Parent / Guardian name
call any school building...Main Street phone # 217-774-4731
or you can sign-up electronically via a form @ this link: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdlkl0Z1KPNDhQddCkUfy4vPl7OaHlgE9eDPlaI6KeSvhTXxg/viewform?usp=sf_link
We plan to provide this daily during the week...sign-up now & we will get your kids meals prepared!
We are in this together; we are a RAMS Family!

post_text: Main Street Music Student-Leaders!
shared_text:
Main Street Elementary School & Kindergarten Center
March 5 at 8:52 AM ·

(9) Main Street 3rd Grade Student-Leaders selected to participate in the Illinois Music Educator Association (ILMEA) General Music Festival (GMF) w/ Mrs. Emily Miller-Amato @ Eastern Illinois University (EIU) Wednesday, March 4th w/ (3) mini-sessions-(Taiko drumming, orff & creative movement), dress rehearsal & a live performance for an audience of parents & music educators @ 5:30 PM.
We are very PROUD of these Student-Leaders already identified w/ a passion for Music to represent themselves & Shelbyville Schools & Community.
Congratulations: Karley Bland, Amelia Bonny, Case Darnell, Myah Gathe, Jackson Harper, Alyson Kazmer, Adalyn Pearcy, Mason Radloff, Leah Shoaff
